# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fabric CI/CD Deployment — Environment Variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to scripts/.env.deploy and fill in the values for local runs.
# In GitHub Actions, add these as repository Secrets (Settings → Secrets → Actions).
#
# ⚠  NEVER commit .env.deploy — it is already in .gitignore
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Fabric Workspace ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The GUID of the Fabric workspace that has Git integration enabled.
# Find it in the URL: https://app.fabric.microsoft.com/groups/<WORKSPACE_ID>/...
FABRIC_WORKSPACE_ID=""


# ── Azure / Entra ID ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for GitHub Actions OIDC and service principal auth.
# For local development these can be left blank — az login is used instead.

# The App Registration (service principal) client ID.
# This SP must have "Admin" or "Contributor" role on the Fabric workspace.
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=""

# Your Azure AD / Entra ID tenant ID.
AZURE_TENANT_ID=""

# Service principal client secret — only needed when NOT using OIDC.
# Leave blank if using GitHub Actions federated credentials (recommended).
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET=""

# Azure subscription ID — required by the azure/login@v2 action.
AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=""


# ── Fabric SQL Connection ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ODBC connection string for the Fabric SQL analytics endpoint.
# Used by setup_sql_views.py to create the views needed by Power BI.
#
# How to get this value:
#   Fabric workspace → agentic_lake → SQL analytics endpoint
#   → Settings → SQL endpoint → copy "SQL connection string"
#   → Change Authentication=ActiveDirectoryInteractive
#     to   Authentication=ActiveDirectoryCli
#
FABRIC_SQL_CONNECTION_URL_AGENTIC=""


# ── Direct Deployment extras (direct_deploy_fabric.py only) ──────────────────
# Only needed for the direct API approach (deploy-fabric-direct.yml).
# Not required for the Git-sync approach (deploy-fabric.yml).

# SQL analytics server hostname — used to auto-patch expressions.tmdl.
# Fabric workspace → agentic_lake → SQL analytics endpoint
# → Settings → SQL endpoint → copy the hostname portion only.
# Example: x1y2z3.datawarehouse.fabric.microsoft.com
FABRIC_SQL_ANALYTICS_SERVER=""

# Lakehouse item GUID — used to auto-patch expressions.tmdl.
# Found in the browser address bar when viewing the SQL analytics endpoint:
#   …/groups/<workspace-id>/lakehouses/<THIS-GUID>
FABRIC_LAKEHOUSE_GUID=""
